<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-14-0625 </DOCNO><TEXT>As accurate an assessment as possible was made of the overall exposureof the US population from all sources of ionizing radiation. These sourceswere categorized according to the origin of the exposure: natural radiation,occupational, the nuclear fuel cycle, consumer products, miscellaneousenvironmental sources connected with human activities, and medical diagnosisand therapy. This report provides a comprehensive account of the exposureof members of the US public to all sources of ionizing radiation. 77refs., 1 fig., 21 tabs.</TEXT></DOC>